---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const description =
  'FocusPing Privacy Policy — no data collected, on-device storage only, optional Reminders import.';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy" description={description} path="/privacy">
  <Nav />
  <main class="legal container">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="updated">Last updated: June 14, 2026</p>

    <p>
      FocusPing ("we", "our", or "the app") is built with privacy as a default. We do not collect,
      sell, or share your personal data. Everything stays on your device.
    </p>

    <h2>Data we do not collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>No account or sign-in required</li>
      <li>No analytics or tracking SDKs</li>
      <li>No advertising identifiers</li>
      <li>No cloud sync of your pings or queue</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Data stored on your device</h2>
    <p>
      Pings, queue state, history, and settings are stored locally using Apple's SwiftData framework.
      This data is not transmitted to our servers because we do not operate servers that receive user data.
    </p>

    <h2>Apple Reminders import (optional)</h2>
    <p>
      If you choose to import reminders, FocusPing reads reminders from Apple's Reminders app on your
      device to create local pings. Imported data is copied on-device only. We do not access your
      Reminders unless you explicitly grant permission and tap Import.
    </p>

    <h2>Focus Status</h2>
    <p>
      With your permission, FocusPing reads your system Focus status to hold ping delivery during Focus
      modes. This status is used locally to decide when to queue notifications. It is not sent off your device.
    </p>

    <h2>Notifications</h2>
    <p>
      FocusPing schedules local notifications on your device. Notification content is generated locally
      from your pings. We do not receive notification delivery data.
    </p>

    <h2>Widgets & App Group</h2>
    <p>
      The home screen widget and Live Activity read queue counts and Deep Work state from a shared App Group
      container on your device. This data is not shared with third parties.
    </p>

    <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
    <p>
      FocusPing is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect data from children.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this policy as the app evolves. Material changes will be reflected on this page with
      an updated date.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about privacy? Email us at
      <a href="mailto:support@focusping.app">support@focusping.app</a> or visit our
      <a href="/support">support page</a>.
    </p>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
